⚙️ 3) PRODUCTION — DATA VALIDATION (VERY IMPORTANT)
🔥 Core Idea

👉 Data validation ensures:

Correct data → Correct system behavior
🧠 Why this matters
Without validation:
wrong calculations
system crashes
financial losses
🔥 Types of Validation
✔ 1. Schema Validation

👉 check structure

if "amount" not in record:
    raise ValueError
✔ 2. Value Validation
if amount <= 0:
    raise ValueError
✔ 3. Type Validation
if not isinstance(amount, float):
    raise TypeError
✔ 4. Business Validation

👉 domain rules

withdrawal <= balance
🔥 Real-Time Usage
Banking System
negative transactions ❌
invalid account ❌
Trading System
invalid price ❌
out-of-range quantity ❌
Data Pipelines
malformed records ❌
corrupted data ❌
🔥 Production Strategy
✔ Validate early

👉 at input stage

✔ Fail fast

👉 stop bad data immediately

✔ Log validation errors
logger.error("Invalid record", extra={"record": record})
✔ Don’t crash entire system

👉 skip bad records

🧠 GS-Level Answer

👉 “How do you validate data?”

💬 Strong Answer:

“I validate data at multiple levels, including schema, type, and business rules. I perform validation early in the pipeline to prevent invalid data from propagating. I log validation failures with context and ensure the system handles errors gracefully without crashing.”

⚠️ Common Mistakes

❌ no validation
❌ validating too late
❌ not logging errors

